		<a name="top" id="top"></a>
		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Light therapy</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:202px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Bright_light_lamp.jpg" class="image" title="Bright light therapy is a common treatment for seasonal affective disorder and for circadian rhythm disorders."><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8d/Bright_light_lamp.jpg/200px-Bright_light_lamp.jpg" width="200" height="144" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Bright_light_lamp.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="/skins-1.5/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
Bright light therapy is a common treatment for seasonal affective disorder and for circadian rhythm disorders.</div>
</div>
</div>
<p><b>Light therapy</b> or <b>phototherapy</b> consists of exposure to daylight or to specific wavelengths of light using <a href="/wiki/Lasers" title="Lasers" class="mw-redirect">lasers</a>, <a href="/wiki/Light-emitting_diode" title="Light-emitting diode">LEDs</a>, <a href="/wiki/Fluorescent_lamps" title="Fluorescent lamps" class="mw-redirect">fluorescent lamps</a>, <a href="/wiki/Dichroic" title="Dichroic" class="mw-redirect">dichroic</a> lamps or very bright, full-spectrum <a href="/wiki/Light" title="Light">light</a>, for a prescribed amount of time and, in some cases, at a specific time of day. It has proven effective in treating <i><a href="/wiki/Acne_vulgaris" title="Acne vulgaris">Acne vulgaris</a>,</i> <a href="/wiki/Seasonal_affective_disorder" title="Seasonal affective disorder">seasonal affective disorder</a>, <a href="/wiki/Neonatal_jaundice" title="Neonatal jaundice">neonatal jaundice</a>, and is part of the standard treatment regimen for <a href="/wiki/Delayed_sleep_phase_syndrome" title="Delayed sleep phase syndrome">delayed sleep phase syndrome</a>. It has recently been shown effective in <a href="/wiki/Clinical_depression" title="Clinical depression" class="mw-redirect">non-seasonal depression</a>. Proponents claim demonstrable benefits for skin conditions such as <a href="/wiki/Psoriasis" title="Psoriasis">psoriasis</a>.</p>
